#### text ####
text: Hakodate was one of the few ports that foreigners could visit when Japan opened up to the world in the 1800s, and was quite small prior to that. As a result, it has a lot of European-style architecture, since that was exotic and exciting at the time the historic city was built up. Some buildings have a mix of European and Japanese styles, including this one where the top was European-style and the bottom was Japanese-style!
