text: Prior to the Seikan tunnel connecting Hokkaido by rail, they had a ferry between Aomori and Hakodate. When the tunnel opened and the ferry service retired, two of the boats were turned into museums on either end, and we visited both! The one in Hakodate is the Mashumaru.
