text: We visited several museums about the Ainu and the other native peoples of northern Japan during the trip. The first was the Hakodate City Museum of Northern Peoples. This was from the perspective of the Japanese, and focused on authentic historic artifacts. The designs the Ainu put on their clothes are beautiful and iconic.
