#### text ####
text: James was very excited about Sapporo-style ramen since it's quite different from the Tokyo-style ramen that we get in Vancouver. Our first dinner was at Sumire, which is famous for its thick miso ramen broth. The rich broth paired perfectly with the vinegared chashu (pork meat) side. Additionally, we got a tip from a local thanks to our Japanese about their favourite ramen shop. It was well off the beaten path in a residential district, and probably doesn't get tourists much. The broth was a mix of pork and seafood with yuzu jelly topping - different and very good!
