#### text ####
text: The final Ainu museum we visited was Upopoy and it was definitely the biggest, fanciest and most corporate of the three. It had a huge museum area, and a traditional style kotan (Ainu for village) behind, connect with a tiny bus. While the other two museums were pretty quiet, Upopoy had a constant stream of Japanese salarymen arriving in tour buses.
